ygData.messageBody:
I think you hit the point about rangers, those
that dont like rangers dont know how to play them.
Even on a non PVP server, Cazic-Thule, knowing what to
do in a group and solo makes a ranger a very good
class to play. I was solo until about lvl 35 then
joined a guild and have had some great times in some
places that I would never had been able to handle solo.
Velious is where I spend all my time now. I travel to
Surefall now and again to keep in touch with my roots but
the frozen waste is where I like to
hunt.<br><br>Keban Arrowsmith<br>Ranger of 43 Seasons<br>Grand
Master Fletcher<br>Cazic-thule
